        "I have already seen a few tests (e.g.: `test/regression/issue_852.py` and `test/regression/issue_676.py`) that use `r.db('name').wait().run(conn)`. This is probably the wrong thing to do, and might in some circumstance not wait for what we assume it should. At a minimum it should use the `wait_for='all_replicas_ready'` flag. We should audit all uses of `wait()` in the testing codebase to make sure we are doing the correct thing.\n"
